GOLDEN Arrows have confirmed the appointment of Lehlohonolo Seema as their new head coach ahead of the 2021-22 DStv Premiership campaign. Seema joins Arrows after a short stint with Chippa United where he helped tem retain teir top flight status in the promotion/ relegation play-offs. He replaces Mandla Ncikazi who helped Abafana Besthende to finish in position four in the log. Ncikazi left Arrows last month to join Orlando Pirates. "We are pleased to announce the appointment of Lehlohonolo Seema as our new head coach," the club said in a brief statement released on Twitter. "We wish him well in the position and look forward to the continuation of growth in the side." We are pleased to announce the appointment of Lehlohonolo Seema as our new Head Coach.We wish him well in the position and look forward to the continuation of growth in the side.#OurStoryContinues pic.twitter.com/45mEfGunN5  